        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(agents): cache provider tool schema normalization",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Cache provider-normalized tool schema `parameters` for repeated embedded agent turns, but only when OpenClaw can identify one of its bundled SDK tool-compat normalizers.\n- Keep the cache internal and conservative: bundled DeepSeek, Gemini, and OpenAI compatibility helpers can reuse cloned normalized `parameters`; custom provider `normalizeToolSchemas` hooks bypass the cache.\n- Avoid new public provider plugin contracts and avoid new operator-facing runtime flags. Tool objects, execute closures, approval state, guards, and runtime policy are still rebuilt per turn.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: repeated embedded agent turns can avoid redoing bundled provider tool-schema compatibility normalization when the provider/model/api/schema signature is unchanged. Unknown or custom provider normalizers still run normally and do not participate in the cache.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS, branch `tool-schema-cache-pr3`, current PR head `4dd1cdbce94d12e7b03ad5930ddd85dd1151a835`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran a terminal proof with `node --import tsx proof.mjs` against the production `normalizeProviderToolSchemas` entry. The script used the real bundled OpenAI tool-schema normalizer identity (`normalizeOpenAIToolSchemas`) through a provider runtime handle, called normalization twice with the same provider/model/api/schema signature and different `execute` closures, then repeated the same pattern with a custom provider normalizer.\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal output from the current head:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"head\": \"4dd1cdbce94d12e7b03ad5930ddd85dd1151a835\",\n  \"bundledCompat\": {\n    \"afterFirst\": { \"bypass\": 0, \"hit\": 0, \"miss\": 1, \"store\": 1, \"size\": 1 },\n    \"afterSecond\": { \"bypass\": 0, \"hit\": 1, \"miss\": 1, \"store\": 1, \"size\": 1 },\n    \"cacheHitIncreasedOnSecondNormalize\": true,\n    \"normalizedParametersEqual\": true,\n    \"secondRunExecuteClosurePreserved\": true\n  },\n  \"customProvider\": {\n    \"customNormalizeCalls\": 2,\n    \"afterCustom\": { \"bypass\": 2, \"hit\": 0, \"miss\": 0, \"store\": 0, \"size\": 0 },\n    \"customProviderBypassedCache\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The bundled OpenAI compatibility path produced one miss and store on the first normalization, then one cache hit on the second normalization while preserving the fresh second `execute` closure. The custom provider path bypassed the cache twice and invoked its normalizer twice, proving the cache remains internal to known bundled compatibility helpers.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full live-provider latency and a remote LLM turn were not tested in this current-head refresh. This PR caches only provider-normalized schema `parameters`; it does not cache complete tool inventory/materialization, policy resolution, prompt inputs, or full agent-turn startup.",
